revised_title: A Case Study of a Foetus Voided per Anum and Fossils Found in Ireland
tldr: The author presents a case study of a woman who experienced a rare pregnancy complication, where a foetus was voided per anum. The woman also passed 80 or more bones of her foetus over a period of 12 months. Additionally, the author discusses fossils found in Ireland, including lac lunae and native vitriol.
